               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18351214-name-196" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18351214-name-196" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18351214-name-196" type="surname" value="OLIVER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18351214-name-196" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN OLIVER</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in pump-court, whitrcross-alley, I was going home on the 28th of November, between half-past eleven and twelve o'clock at night and saw Charles Dalton drunk in the street—I saw the prisoner take the coat off his back—he went away with it—he first said he was a friend of his, and asked me and the other witness to move him—we took him to pump-court, and thought the prisoner was following us, but he went away.</p>
               <p>
