                  </hi>. I am a hair-dresser, and live in Circus-street, Bryanstone-square, I met prisoner at half-past eight o'clock on Saturday evening—we drank at the Red Lion, and then removed to another public-house, and drank till eleven o'clock—I lost a cost off my back, also four razors, a knife, apron, two pair of stockings, and pair of scissors—I did not authorize any body to take it off—I was quite insensible.</p>
